.TH VALIDATE-AUTONOMOUS-RUN-STATE 1 "2026-07-14" "autonomous-run-governance 0.2.0" "User Commands"
.SH NAME
validate-autonomous-run-state \- validate resumable autonomous Spec Kit run state
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B bash validate-autonomous-run-state.sh
.BI --state " FILE"
.PP
.B pwsh -NoProfile -File validate-autonomous-run-state.ps1
.BI -State " FILE"
.SH DESCRIPTION
Validates the feature-local autonomous-run-state JSON schema, checkpoint fields,
task counters, lifecycle state, stop boundary, and authority revalidation flag.
The validator is read-only and grants no start, resume, commit, push, merge, or
provider authority.
.SH STATES
Allowed states are Active, StopRequested, PausedByUser, Interrupted, Blocked,
and Completed. Paused, interrupted, and blocked states require an explicit stop
reason, UTC request time, safe boundary, and later authority revalidation.
.SH EXIT STATUS
Returns 0 when the state is valid and 2 for invalid input or schema violations.
.SH PORTABILITY
Invoke the installed Bash script explicitly through bash because ZIP extraction
may not preserve executable mode bits. Use PowerShell 7 on Windows.
